    <item>
      <title>1. Installation</title>
      <link>https://bladeos.xyz/docs/v24/installing/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://bladeos.xyz/docs/v24/installing/</guid>
      <description>&lt;div class=&#34;tip tip_warning&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Installing Blade OS can erase your hard drive. Please make sure you have everything backed up before proceeding.&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;download-the-iso&#34; class=link_owner&gt;&#xA;  Download the ISO&#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;#download-the-iso&#34; class=&#34;link icon&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;svg&gt;&#xA;      &lt;use xlink:href=&#34;#anchor-link&#34;&gt;&lt;/use&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;First, You&amp;rsquo;ll need to download the latest Blade OS ISO, Which can be found here.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;../../../download&#34; class=&#34;button&#34;&gt;Download&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;preparing-the-installation-media&#34; class=link_owner&gt;&#xA;  Preparing the installation media&#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;#preparing-the-installation-media&#34; class=&#34;link icon&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;svg&gt;&#xA;      &lt;use xlink:href=&#34;#anchor-link&#34;&gt;&lt;/use&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tip&#34;&gt;&#xA;  If you&amp;rsquo;re using a virtual machine, You may skip this step.&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tip tip_warning&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Burning to external media could potentially erase it. Please make sure you have everything backed up before proceeding.&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;In order to install Blade OS, You&amp;rsquo;ll need an installation media. There&amp;rsquo;s multiple programs that can get the job done.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>2. The Desktop</title>
      <link>https://bladeos.xyz/docs/v24/desktop/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://bladeos.xyz/docs/v24/desktop/</guid>
      <description>&lt;div class=&#34;tip&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Blade OS currently uses the GNOME desktop.&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;the-activities-overview&#34; class=link_owner&gt;&#xA;  The Activities overview&#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;#the-activities-overview&#34; class=&#34;link icon&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;svg&gt;&#xA;      &lt;use xlink:href=&#34;#anchor-link&#34;&gt;&lt;/use&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The activities overview allows you to create virtual desktops to organize their open windows. You can open it by clicking on the &lt;strong&gt;Activites&lt;/strong&gt; button on the top left corner of the screen. You can also open it by pressing the &lt;strong&gt;SUPER&lt;/strong&gt; key.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;../../../images/docs/v24/gnome-desktop.png&#34; alt=&#34;Activities Overview&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;the-app-drawer&#34; class=link_owner&gt;&#xA;  The app drawer&#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;#the-app-drawer&#34; class=&#34;link icon&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;svg&gt;&#xA;      &lt;use xlink:href=&#34;#anchor-link&#34;&gt;&lt;/use&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The app drawer allows you to open your apps. You can open it by clicking on the grid on the right end of the dock. You can also open it by double pressing the &lt;strong&gt;SUPER&lt;/strong&gt; key.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>3. Software Management</title>
      <link>https://bladeos.xyz/docs/v24/software/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://bladeos.xyz/docs/v24/software/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;the-built-in-software-app&#34; class=link_owner&gt;&#xA;  The built-in Software app&#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;#the-built-in-software-app&#34; class=&#34;link icon&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;svg&gt;&#xA;      &lt;use xlink:href=&#34;#anchor-link&#34;&gt;&lt;/use&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Blade OS comes with the built in &lt;strong&gt;Software&lt;/strong&gt; app, which allows you to download new apps and update existing apps and your entire system with ease.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Blade OS supports two ways of installing &amp;amp; updating applications:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;APT - Built in package manager for Blade OS&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Flatpak - An extensive library of applications &amp;amp; games you can install&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;explore&#34; class=link_owner&gt;&#xA;  Explore&#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;#explore&#34; class=&#34;link icon&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;svg&gt;&#xA;      &lt;use xlink:href=&#34;#anchor-link&#34;&gt;&lt;/use&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;You can explore &amp;amp; search for new apps in this section.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>4. System Backups</title>
      <link>https://bladeos.xyz/docs/v24/timeshift/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://bladeos.xyz/docs/v24/timeshift/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;timeshift&#34; class=link_owner&gt;&#xA;  Timeshift&#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;#timeshift&#34; class=&#34;link icon&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;svg&gt;&#xA;      &lt;use xlink:href=&#34;#anchor-link&#34;&gt;&lt;/use&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Blade OS comes with the built in &lt;strong&gt;Timeshift&lt;/strong&gt; app, which allows administrators to backup &amp;amp; restore their system with ease.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;setup-wizzard&#34; class=link_owner&gt;&#xA;  Setup Wizzard&#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;#setup-wizzard&#34; class=&#34;link icon&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;svg&gt;&#xA;      &lt;use xlink:href=&#34;#anchor-link&#34;&gt;&lt;/use&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;If you&amp;rsquo;re using the app for the first time, you&amp;rsquo;ll be met with the setup wizzard.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;snapshot-type&#34; class=link_owner&gt;&#xA;  Snapshot Type&#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;#snapshot-type&#34; class=&#34;link icon&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;svg&gt;&#xA;      &lt;use xlink:href=&#34;#anchor-link&#34;&gt;&lt;/use&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;There&amp;rsquo;s two types of snapshots you can use:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;rsync&#34; class=link_owner&gt;&#xA;  RSYNC&#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;#rsync&#34; class=&#34;link icon&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;svg&gt;&#xA;      &lt;use xlink:href=&#34;#anchor-link&#34;&gt;&lt;/use&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The slow &amp;amp; recommended way.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
